Vice President Joe Biden had a call with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko to discuss the situation in eastern Ukraine. President Poroshenko informed Biden about Russia's direct involvement in the conflict, with incidents of ordnance being fired at Ukrainian military forces from the Russian side of the border. They expressed concern about Russia's statements suggesting a role for Russian "peacekeepers" in Ukraine, the ongoing military buildup on Ukraine's border, and the continued transfer of weapons to Russian proxies in Ukraine. President Poroshenko reiterated his commitment to avoiding civilian casualties and minimizing collateral damage while restoring law and order in eastern Ukraine. They also discussed the possibilities for a diplomatic resolution to the crisis.